{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"104f6b69-bf21-4e6b-84f1-ebec1ace9407","content":"In xUnit v3 with MTP, the VSTest filter syntax (`--filter`) is replaced by the `--filter` option using **MTP filter expressions**, which have different syntax.\n\n**Your old filter (VSTest):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**Translated for xUnit v3 + MTP:**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n\n| VSTest | MTP (xUnit v3) |\n|--------|-----------------|\n| `&` | `and` |\n| `\\|` | `or` |\n| `!` | `not` |\n| `~` (contains) | `~` (still works) |\n\nThe operators become **words** (`and`, `or`, `not`) instead of symbols. The `~` (contains) operator and `=` (equals) remain the same. The `Category` trait property is still recognized because xUnit v3 surfaces `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` as a filterable property.\n\nSo your CI command becomes:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5fcdaafd-3676-4bb5-8f9f-1b7b04d23dba","outputTokens":304,"requestId":"BC28:17168D:1C586E2:1F6F793:69FA90FB"},"id":"0b6c2749-1858-47c3-8598-43969c6cb6b8","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:53:24.108Z","parentId":"9883b33d-8caa-4840-88af-df923a67eb12"}
